                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-310-off1661 t18230910-310-victim2667"></join>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230910-310-person2668">
                  THOMAS 
                  RIGBY
               <interp inst="t18230910-310-person2668" type="surname" value="RIGBY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-310-person2668" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-310-person2668" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in the New-road, St. George's. On the 17th of August, about half-past nine o'clock, I was in <placeName id="t18230910-310-crimeloc1663">Whitechapel-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-310-crimeloc1663" type="placeName" value="Whitechapel-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-310-crimeloc1663" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-310-off1661 t18230910-310-crimeloc1663"></join>; I had a child in my arms, and my housekeeper by my side. I passed a doctor's shop, at the corner of <placeName id="t18230910-310-crimeloc1664">North-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-310-crimeloc1664" type="placeName" value="North-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-310-crimeloc1664" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-310-off1661 t18230910-310-crimeloc1664"></join> - the prisoner gave me a shove and turned me right round - there was a gas-light at the corner, and at the doctor's shop also - he came from behind, and shoved me, turned me right round, and snatched my watch from my fob, and ran up North-street - I pursued, calling out Stop thief! he was not taken then - I saw him in custody four days after, and cannot swear to him, as I only saw his back.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. ALLEY. Q. Did you recover your watch - A. Yes; it was sent to me a week or ten days after.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230910-310-person2669">
                  SARAH 
                  RIGBY
               <interp inst="t18230910-310-person2669" type="surname" value="RIGBY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-310-person2669" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-310-person2669" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in company with Mrs. Rigby, walking on his left side - he was carrying the child. I noticed a man following us, and looked round several times, thinking he knew us - he was alone. At the corner of North-street, he came behind us and gave Mr. Rigby a shove on the left shoulder, I did not see him snatch the watch - he ran down North-street; an alarm was given. Mr. Rigby ran after him - I took the child from him, and another person came behind and threw him down - I saw the prisoner in custody on the 22d - there was a gas light from the shop, and one from the corner - I believe him to be the man, and am sure that he is.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. You never knew him before - A. No; I never fixed on any other - I was coming out of a friend's house in North-street, and Mr. Rigby said,</p>
               <p>"This looks like the man who tripped me up." I said,</p>
               <p>"It is not him, for he was a great deal taller." I described him to the officers, and when I saw the prisoner, I was certain of him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230910-310-person2670">
                  GEORGE 
                  ELLIS
               <interp inst="t18230910-310-person2670" type="surname" value="ELLIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-310-person2670" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-310-person2670" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. Mr. and Mrs. Rigby gave me a description of the men on the Monday after the robbery, and in consequence of the woman's description, I apprehended the prisoner on the Wednesday following. I knew him before. The woman never hesitated about him.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18230910-310-verdict1665" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18230910-310-verdict1665" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 20.</p>
